<UNK>Scuffle, Arrests Mar Gay Pride Festival</UNK>
<DATELINE>SANTA ANA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A shouting match between homosexuals and
fundamentalist Christians erupted into a brawl during Orange
County's first gay-pride festival.
   Six people were arrested Sunday for investigation of failure to
obey police during the scuffle, which involved 30 to 40 people in a
gay-pride parade and an unspecified number of protesters, said
