<SECOND>AM-BRF--Post Editors,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Palm Beach Post Makes Editorial Changes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Palm Beach Post has named Tom
O'Hara managing editor and Randy Schultz associate editor of the
editorial page, the newspaper reported.
   Schultz, 37, who has been managing editor since 1985, will
succeed Clarke Ash, 65, as editorial page editor in January. Ash
will continue writing a column for The Post.
   O'Hara, 42, had been assistant managing editor and metro editor
since February.
   John Bartosek, 36, has been named assistant managing editor and
Price Patton, 39, has been named metro editor. The promotions were
announced by Post Editor Edward Sears and were effective immediately.
   Schultz worked for The Miami Herald before coming to The Post in
1976, where he served in several key editorial positions. O'Hara
joined the Post in 1986 after eight years as a reporter and editor
for The Miami Herald.
