<HEAD>Bush Names New Assistant Education Secretary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Monday announced he would
nominate Leonard L. Haynes III, a Louisiana educator, to be
assistant secretary of education for postsecondary education.
   Haynes, 42, currently is assistant superintendent for academic
programs at Louisiana State University in Baton Rouge. He is a
