<DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A government official
said 12 bodies were recovered and only nine survivors were reported
Monday from a boat carrying 70 illegal emigrants that capsized last
week.
   Civil Defense Director Eugenio Cabral said the Dominican Navy
discontinued its search for further victims Monday night.
   The Civil Defense said the boat set set sail from the Dominican
Republic's east coast and capsized on Sept. 5 three miles off
Higuey, 145 miles east of Santo Domingo, the capital.
   Scores of Dominican illegals try to reach Puerto Rico each week
through the Mona Passage, which separates the Dominican Republic
from Puerto Rico.
   An anonymous source in Higuey said Monday that four bodies were
recovered Sunday night and were buried at once in the beach because
of their advanced state of decomposition.
   The nine known survivors were treated in Higuey Hospital for
dehydration, exposure and bruises.
