   A cookbook for visually impaired cooks - in large type and in
braille - is being offered by the NutraSweet Company.
   The 60-page collection features low-calorie recipes for
appetizers, beverages, entrees, salads and desserts, using the
company's Equal sweetener.
   The book grew out of a suggestion by Jill Noble of the Cleveland
Society for the Blind. She and Phyllis Rosenthal, consumer affairs
analyst for Equal, converted a series of recipes to braille and
large type. Each of the 70 recipes was re-tested and modified for
use by cooks with little or no sight.
