<TEXT>
   Campeau Corp., the debt-laden Canadian developer
and owner of numerous retail businesses, proposed a major financial
overhaul that includes the sale of Bloomingdale's, one of the best
known store chains.
   Bloomingdale's Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Marvin S.
Traub has indicated Friday he would like to participate in a
possible management buyout.
   Wall Street analysts said Campeau's willingness to part with
Bloomingdale's underscored the severity of the financial
difficulties facing the company.
