oats were \ cent lower to 1 cent higher with September at $1.39 a
bushel; soybeans were 4{ cents lower to 1 cent higher and September
was at $6.03 a bushel.
   Cattle futures were mostly higher while pork futures were mixed
in early trading on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange.
   Live cattle were .02 cent lower to .38 cent higher with October
at 72.02 cents a pound; feeder cattle were .07 cent to .45 cent
higher with September at 82.30 cents a pound; live hogs were .40
cent lower to .15 cent higher with October at 38.77 cents a pound;
frozen pork bellies were .15 cent to .30 cent higher with February
at 46.05 cents a pound.
   Livestock and meat futures settled lower on Friday.
