<FIRST>r f BC-CoalProdn     09-11 0107</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Coal Prodn,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 20.1 million
short tons during the week ending Sept. 2, up slightly from the 20
million short tons produced in the previous week, the Department of
Energy reported Monday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 19.9 million short tons in the
same week last year, according to the department's Energy
Information Administration.
   A short ton is equal to 2,000 pounds.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 642.4 million short
tons, 2.9 percent above last year's production at this time, the
agency said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
</TEXT>
