<HEAD>Industry Reports Decline in Weekly Production</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic steel production totaled 1,695,000 net
tons during the week ending Saturday, down 0.6 percent from the
previous week, the American Iron and Steel Institute reported Monday.
   The week's production represented 76.3 percent of the industry's
domestic capacity, according to the steel industry group.
   American steelmakers produced 1,921,000 net tons in the same week
last year, AISI said.
   Domestic steel production so far this year is 69,240,000 net
tons, 0.1 percent below last year's production at this time, AISI
said.
