<FIRST>r f BC-Seagram-Stock     09-11 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Seagram-Stock,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Seagram Announces Share Repurchase Plan</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Seagram Co. Ltd. Monday said its board of directors authorized
the purchase of up to 5 percent of its common stock.
   Seagram, a leading maker and marketer of distilled spirits and
wine, said the shares will be bought from time to time during the 12
months beginning Sept. 25. The purchases will be made through
exchanges in Montreal, where Seagram is based, Toronto and New York.
   Under a repurchase program due to expire Sept. 23, Seagram bought
more than 2.48 million shares of its common stock from the open
market as of Aug. 28 at an average price of $71.50 a share. On Aug.
28, there were 96.01 million shares of Seagram common stock
outstanding.
   Companies use share repurchase programs for a variety of reasons.
Sometimes when a company thinks its stock is trading at too low a
value, it buys back shares to boost the price.
</TEXT>
