<FIRST>r f BC-Daimler-MBB     09-11 0192</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Daimler-MBB,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>Daimler-Benz Accepts Conditions For MBB Merger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STUTTGART, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Automotive giant Daimler-Benz on
Monday accepted the conditions set by Economics Minister Helmut
Haussmann for its planned takeover of a majority in the aerospace
and defense concern Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm.
   That means that West Germany's largest postwar merger can now be
formally completed before the end of the year, officials said.
   Although the diversified automaker said the conditions would have
a sizable impact on the company, Chairman Edzard Reuter told
reporters they were ``just within the limits of what could be
accepted without putting into question the total industrial
concept'' it had in mind.
   The Bonn government on Friday approved the merger on condition
that Daimler spin off certain Daimler and MBB defense technology
activities, that Daimler executives give up certain outside board
seats, and that it relieve the government of a stake in the troubled
European Airbus aerospace consortium three years earlier than
planned.
   Daimler said its approval is conditional on a similar nod from
MBB's current owners. But Reuter said he had ``no doubt'' that
Daimler would formally have completed the merger by the end of the
year.
</TEXT>
