<FILEID>AP-NR-09-11-89 2241EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Mexico-Iacocca     09-11 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Mexico-Iacocca,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Iacocca Meets with Mexican President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. Chairman Lee Iacocca met with
President Carlos Salinas de Gortari on Monday and said that Mexico
needs to become more competitive in the world trade arena, Mexican
news agencies reported.
   ``What is needed now is to be competitive on the international
level, attract investment and technology,'' Iacocca told the
independent news agency Excelsior.
   After a private meeting with Salinas in the presendential
residence, Iacocca described Mexico's achievement of a 20 percent
annual inflation rate as ``stupendous.''
   A government wage-price control plan has brought Mexico's
inflation rate down from 159.2 percent in 1987.
   Iacocca said his company plans new investments in Mexico.
   ``We have been here for 50 years and we'll keep investing,'' he
told the government news agency Notimex. ``There will be a better
future and a stronger economy here.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
